Chelsea welcome Aston Villa to Stamford Bridge on Wednesday night, four days after they lost 1-0 to West Ham on their home patch. The result saw the Blues drop to fourth place, still on 26 points. Villa battled to a 2-2 draw at Manchester United on Sunday, coming back from behind twice to rescue a point. Kick off is 8.30pm West African time. Chelsea XI vs Aston Villa: Kepa, James, Christensen, Zouma, Azpilicueta, Kante, Kovacic, Willian, Mount, Pulisic, Abraham Aston Villa XI vs Chelsea: Heaton, Elmohamady, Konsa, Mings, Targett, McGinn, Nakamba, Hourihane, Trezeguet, Wesley, Grealish Wednesday, December 4 Full time: Chelsea have defeated Aston Villa 2-1. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.